{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q11603258]] Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 07:41, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} '''Kudatama''' (管玉) are tubular components of [[:en:Fashion accessory|jewelry]], classified as a type of [[:en:Bead|bead]], designed for threading onto strings for use in [[:en:Bracelet|bracelets]] or [[:en:Necklace|necklaces]]. In ancient times, they were crafted from rare {{ill|gemstones|ja|宝玉|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/gemstones|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 如意宝珠|1=Cintamani|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q2963837}} such as glass, and in the kanji cultural sphere, they were categorized alongside other bead forms like [[:en:Magatama|magatama]] and [[:en:Glass bead making|tonbo-dama]] under the generic term "gyoku" (玉), meaning "jewel."
